{"id":1195,"date":"2021-07-06T12:41:18","date_gmt":"2021-07-06T10:41:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/?p=1195"},"modified":"2021-07-06T12:41:20","modified_gmt":"2021-07-06T10:41:20","slug":"triple-and-neanias-sign-memorandum-of-understanding","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/2021\/07\/triple-and-neanias-sign-memorandum-of-understanding\/","title":{"rendered":"TRIPLE and NEANIAS Sign Memorandum of Understanding"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p>In early June, TRIPLE signed a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/NEANIAS-TRIPLE-MoU_final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Memorandum of Understanding<\/a> (MoU) with <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.neanias.eu\/\" target=\"_blank\">NEANIAS<\/a> with the aim to foster a collabaration between two projects which are financed under the European Union\u2019s <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/ec.europa.eu\/programmes\/horizon2020\/what-horizon-2020\" target=\"_blank\">Horizon 2020<\/a> Research and Innovation action funding scheme <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/eosc-portal.eu\/infraeosc-02-2019-prototyping-new-innovative-services\" target=\"_blank\">INFRAEOSC-02-2019 \u201cPrototyping new innovative services\u201d<\/a>. This makes NEANIAS and TRIPLE two complementary European Open Science Cloud (EOSC) projects in the domain of Open Science.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/NEANIAS-TRIPLE-MoU_final.pdf\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"453\" height=\"599\" src=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/MoU-NEANIAS-TRIPLE.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1198\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/MoU-NEANIAS-TRIPLE.jpg 453w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/MoU-NEANIAS-TRIPLE-227x300.jpg 227w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\" \/><\/a><figcaption><a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/NEANIAS-TRIPLE-MoU_final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MoU between NEANIAS and TRIPLE<\/a><\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>The acronym NEANIAS stands for \u201cNovel EOSC services for Emerging Atmosphere, Underwater and Space Challenges\u201d. The NEANIAS project, which lasts 36 months and involves 20 partners from 9 European countries, is a focused Open Science project in the field of co-design and delivery of innovative thematic services, derived from state-of-the-art research assets and practices in three major sectors: Underwater, atmospheric and space research.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Considering the fact that NEANIAS and TRIPLE are two initiatives in the field of data research, the MoU is targeted at bilateral information exchange and collaboration. This will benefit the respective goals of both projects, especially in the areas of communication &amp; outreach, dissemination, validation and exploitation activities. It will ultimately help us join forces in our Open Science ambitions.<\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In early June, TRIPLE signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with NEANIAS with the aim to foster a collabaration between two projects which are financed under the European Union\u2019s Horizon 2020 Research and Innovation action funding scheme INFRAEOSC-02-2019 \u201cPrototyping new<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":1203,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[23],"tags":[19,15],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotripl